Absolutely fabulous!!! I've been using this recipe since it appeared as the "cover bird" on Gourmet magazine years ago - it's a family favorite. Just follow the directions and it's fool proof every time. It is not our custom to carve the bird at the table and I don't use the pan drippings for gravy. Instead I strain the drippings, discard the fat, reheat to almost boiling, then pour the drippings over the cut meat to freshen up the flavour - then bring to the table. Delicious every time. Enjoy

