Three stars for the shiitake mushroom gravy. Very good and rich tasting. I used tawny port instead of sherry, and homemade turkey stock instead of canned chicken broth. I had major problems with the roux. It curdled so badly that I had to use an electric whisk to remove the lumps, and it splattered all over the stove top. I think the right technique is to add hot liquids into the roux, not the other way around. The gravy also tasted better the next day. Next time, I will make it one day in advance, and add pan juices at the last minute. Less stressful.

