Rating: 4
This recipe produces a "perfectly" cooked turkey...crisp,golden skin and moist tender meat! I take the turkey out of the oven when the deepest part of the breast is at 161 degrees farenheight. After the 30 minutes rest period, it will rise to approximately 170 degrees, with the carry over cooking. This ensures that you will never end up with dry breast meat! I took the advise of previuos reviewers and put some of the herb mixture under the skin. This seemed to help add flavor to the meat itself. I couldn't find shiitake mushrooms, so I used baby portabello with great results. I only used a splash of cream to finish the gravy...it was wonderful. This recipe is so good that I often make a 12 pound turkey for a non holiday dinner. Everyone loves it and the leftovers make great hot turkey sandwiches the next day. What a treat!!

