Rating: 4
This was my best turkey yet but my modification was to soak the turkey in brine for 12 hrs. 1 quart water, 1/2 cup salt, 1/4 cup sugar, boil with herbs and cool. Put bird in large pot cover with brine, top off with ice water and store in room temp. The bacteria is killed off by the brine. Once cooked it squirts out juice at ya so watch out! I make the sauce with portobellos and served it with a Ridge Geyserville Zinfandel 1997. Cranberry cherry sauce, wild rice w/filberts, and sweet potatoes. I was mobbed afterwards, be careful, this recipe may be hazardous to your health.

