Rating: 4
My husband and I made this for dinner tonight using a turkey breast and the fresh herbs in our yard. We followed the temperatures in the recipe's cooking instructions, allowing shorter roasting time for the breast, and it worked just fine. The turkey was incredibly good, and the gravy was truly exceptional. I reconstituted half of a half-ounce package of porcini mushrooms in one-half cup of boiling water to use in the dressing, and saved the strained liquid to use in place of some of the broth in the gravy. Couldn't find fresh shiitake mushrooms, so substituted portabellas. What an awesome meal! My husband had thirds. Tonight's dinner was a dress rehearsal for Thanksgiving, when we have a crowd to cook for, and we will certainly be repeating this again. After thirty years of cooking turkey dinners, this was absolutely the best.

